Yes, but he’s wanting to use the PFAC export to do it and not S&P (I don’t fully understand or remember the difference between the two reports enough to know what’s right and wrong)

I emailed them but haven’t heard back, I’ll let you know once they get back to me and we get a time set.
I can get on a call, yes.
Aren’t they to import into their system and PRODUCE? Which is why the S&P requires item mapping.
Stephen - we will likely need your help on that call

Isaac - can you just write them and tell them at this point, we are still trying to understand what they are trying to accomplish with these reports? Ask them for a call or something. There is no way we can get the right answer to something when no one on our team knows the goal.
I agree with Kevin, I don't fully understand WHAT these individual reports are supposed to do, and I don't think BLN does either, they are wanting like a combo of the two.
Does anyone know what the purpose of these exports is? I'm lost at this point as well. It would be faster to get the purpose and specs of each export and rebuild

PFAC is just an export of this view so removing the NRS records from that view removes it from the export. And you want to have multiple reports that include different sites, but somehow come up with the same output? I don't understand what you're trying to accomplish.

So if we could add those back to that export. 

 

I can see the values are different than the PFAC from before, but they don't match that of the S&P still, but I'm not gonna say it's off until I can do a true side by side comparison of the two.
I don't think they did, Jon kind of did but I don't think BLN as a whole wants that.
Do we know that we don't want NRS stores? I don't think we want to remove those. Isaac - did BLN ask for that?

Okay I've tried several different things, but I can't get the S&P Export to run, it shows it's loading for a bit and then goes away without actually downloading.

 

I was able to download the PFAC export, and I can see that there are no NRS stores on that export anymore.

 

Can you see why the S&P Export wouldn't be loading?
Isaac - make sure we get another response to BLN before end of day
Yeah I would like that more, because without Claude it would’ve taken me forever to figure that out.
Yeah. Or, we could change the join so that the report has an empty value when there isn't a ProductionItem link? That way they know what they are...

Seems like for the 7 items that are missing, they don't have any Production Item link, and all other items do. I THINK to fix that one I need to get BLN to send me the Production Item Links (4 mil numbers) for those items.
Eric what do you think of this? Stephen? I don't have context on the purpose of these reports so I'm lost at this point
I updated the frontend. So it's visually better
It was using the wrong journal. Then I had an issue because it was not importing the quantity, so I had to fix it as well
The frontend doesn't display the statuses correctly. Both show as "Grow", even though 054 - 4 - 2025 is "Ready".
That’s awesome, what did you do to get it to work?
I'm running the importer. It will take a while
I believe I found why we didn't receive the BP Lot No. I'm changing it.
Is there an update i can give BPF right now?
Ethan I'm seeing on changes you push that Claude used a different journal in your changes for grow items. Do you know the reason for that?
how did we find this bug then? i'm very lost on how we discovered this bug for BPF if we were never able to get the BPlot numbers for grow items?
We received the BP Lot No for Organic Ready Items. However, for the GROW items, we do not have that information since they were not imported before, so we can't confirm if it worked previously
how did that happen? Like, didn't we have this working, did NAV change or us?
So we were able to remove the filter to import the Organic grow items, but the items coming back from nav don't have the Lot number.
We imported the item, but we didn't receive the BP Lot No. In NAV, they have different BP lot No
We made some changes in the code, but we are still not importing grow organic items. We are verifying that.
